      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_reset_ctrl_1acbfb668d7b4cfa39aa1a5a5dac3c0e7e" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void task</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Reset control task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>Initially the cyclic timer for power cycle reset (cold start) will be started. Afterwards the function enters the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
<bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eTimerExpired: On metrics TX interval timer expiry the pointer pElem will be set to 0, to prevent releasing the message because it is allocated static. Finally cold start will be initiated by calling function trigger. Since FW 1.74 cold start has been replaced by SW reset.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eColdStartReq: A cold start will be initiated by calling function trigger. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
