    <briefdescription>
<para>Reset Control class derived from task base class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The Reset Control class implements the cyclic power cycle reset (cold start). It controls Pin P0.01 of nRF9160 which can trigger the reset. The cycle period is controlled by a timer. <linebreak/>
 The Reset Control class provide a timer callback function and a timer expired function, used to transform external timer expiry event from interrupt context to internal timer expired message of type <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref>. Furthermore an initialization function and a trigger function, which perform the cold start reset. <bold>Message Interaction:</bold><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Receive<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Timer interrupt callback</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Reset control task (self)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Transmit<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Reset control task (self) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
